# [Conventional Commits Format]
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# [optional body]
#
# Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ATOMIC COMMIT CHECKLIST
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ☐ Does this commit represent ONE logical change?
# ☐ Can I explain the "why" in one sentence?
# ☐ If reverted, does it cleanly undo one thing?
# ☐ Does the codebase still work after THIS commit alone?
# ☐ Are tests passing for THIS commit?
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# COMMIT TYPES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat:     New feature (user-facing)
# fix:      Bug fix (user-facing)
# docs:     Documentation only changes
# style:    Formatting, missing semicolons, etc (no code change)
# refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# perf:     Performance improvement
# test:     Adding/updating tests
# chore:    Maintenance (build, dependencies, configs)
# ci:       CI/CD changes
# build:    Build system or external dependencies
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# COMMON SCOPES (see npm run git:scope for suggestions)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# diagnosis    - Diagnosis wizard, 4-Examination Model
# doctor       - Doctor portal, dashboard, reports
# patient      - Patient dashboard, communication
# auth         - Authentication, login, sessions
# api          - API routes, endpoints
# db           - Database, migrations, schema
# ui           - UI components, design system
# iot          - IoT device integration
# hooks        - Git hooks, Husky configuration
# config       - Configuration files
# deps         - Dependencies, package.json
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EXAMPLES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat(diagnosis): add pulse waveform visualization
#
# Implements real-time pulse waveform display using Canvas API.
# Integrates with IoT pulse sensor data stream.
#
# - Add PulseWaveform component
# - Connect to WebSocket pulse data
# - Add waveform smoothing algorithm
#
# Fixes: #123
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# fix(auth): resolve token refresh on session timeout
#
# Previously, expired tokens caused silent logout. Now properly
# refreshes token before expiry and shows warning to user.
#
# Root cause: setTimeout not cleared on unmount
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# refactor(iot): extract device connection logic
#
# Moves device pairing logic into reusable hook for consistency
# across diagnosis wizard steps.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# BEST PRACTICES
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • Subject: imperative mood ("add" not "added"), max 72 chars
# • Body: explain WHY not WHAT (code shows what)
# • Reference issues: "Fixes: #123" or "Refs: #456"
# • Breaking changes: Add "BREAKING CHANGE:" in body
# • Co-author: Always credit Claude with Co-Authored-By line
#
# Need help? Run: npm run git:scope
